### RxDB Database Creation and Operations with LocalStorage

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs/electron-database.html

Demonstrates how to install RxDB and RxJS, create a database using the LocalStorage RxStorage, add collections, insert documents, perform queries, and observe query results. This snippet is useful for getting started with RxDB in an Electron renderer process.

```javascript
import { createRxDatabase } from 'rxdb';
import { getRxStorageLocalstorage } from 'rxdb/plugins/storage-localstorage';

// create database
const db = await createRxDatabase({
    name: 'exampledb',
    storage: getRxStorageLocalstorage()
});

// create collections
const collections = await db.addCollections({
    humans: {
        /* ... */
    }
});

// insert document
await collections.humans.insert({
    id: 'foo',
    name: 'bar'
});

// run a query
const result = await collections.humans.find({
    selector: {
        name: 'bar'
    }
}).exec();

// observe a query
await collections.humans.find({
    selector: {
        name: 'bar'
    }
}).$.subscribe(result => {/* ... */});
```

