Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs/quickstart.html

This snippet demonstrates how to start WebRTC replication for a collection in RxDB. It utilizes the `replicateWebRTC` function and requires the `getConnectionHandlerSimplePeer` for establishing connections. Ensure you set a unique 'topic' for your application and a 'secret' for security.

```javascript
import {
    replicateWebRTC,
    getConnectionHandlerSimplePeer
} from 'rxdb/plugins/replication-webrtc';

replicateWebRTC({
    collection: myDatabase.todos,
    connectionHandlerCreator: getConnectionHandlerSimplePeer({}),
    topic: '', // <- set any app-specific room id here.
    secret: 'mysecret',
    pull: {},
    push: {}
})
```

