### Add 'todos' Collection with Schema

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/quickstart.md

Adds a 'todos' collection to the RxDB database. The collection is defined with a JSON schema specifying its structure, including fields like 'id', 'name', 'done', and 'timestamp'.

```typescript
await myDatabase.addCollections({
    todos: {
        schema: {
            version: 0,
            primaryKey: 'id',
            type: 'object',
            properties: {
                id: {
                    type: 'string',
                    maxLength: 100
                },
                name: {
                    type: 'string'
                },
                done: {
                    type: 'boolean'
                },
                timestamp: {
                    type: 'string',
                    format: 'date-time'
                }
            },
            required: ['id', 'name', 'done', 'timestamp']
        }
    }
});
```

