### Install Appwrite Server using Docker

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs/replication-appwrite.html

This snippet demonstrates how to install a self-hosted Appwrite instance using Docker. It ensures Docker and Docker Compose are up-to-date and then runs an installation script within a Docker container. The script creates necessary configuration files and sets up the Appwrite environment. It also provides commands to start and stop the Appwrite instance.

```bash
docker-compose -v
docker run -it --rm \
    --volume /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock \
    --volume "$(pwd)"/appwrite:/usr/src/code/appwrite:rw \
    --entrypoint="install" \
    appwrite/appwrite:1.6.1

# stop
docker-compose down
# start
docker-compose up
```

