### Start RxDB Remote WebSocket Server (Node.js)

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs/rx-storage-remote.html

This snippet shows how to start a RxDB remote WebSocket server. It can be initialized either with an existing RxDatabase instance or a standalone RxStorage instance. The server listens on a specified port for incoming client connections.

```javascript
import { getRxStorageMemory } from 'rxdb/plugins/storage-memory';
import { startRxStorageRemoteWebsocketServer } from 'rxdb/plugins/storage-remote-websocket';

// Option 1: Server based on an RxDatabase
const serverBasedOnDatabase = await startRxStorageRemoteWebsocketServer({
    port: 8080,
    database: myRxDatabase
});

// Option 2: Server based on a pure RxStorage
const serverBasedOn = await startRxStorageRemoteWebsocketServer({
    port: 8080,
    storage: getRxStorageMemory()
});
```

