### Start RxDB Websocket Server (Node.js)

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs/replication-websocket.html

This code demonstrates how to initialize a RxDB database and then start a websocket server from it using the 'rxdb/plugins/replication-websocket' plugin. The server listens on a specified port and path. The returned server state object has a 'close' method to shut down the server.

```javascript
import { createRxDatabase } from 'rxdb';
import {
    startWebsocketServer
} from 'rxdb/plugins/replication-websocket';

// create a RxDatabase like normal
const myDatabase = await createRxDatabase({/* ... */});

// start a websocket server
const serverState = await startWebsocketServer({
    database: myDatabase,
    port: 1337,
    path: '/socket'
});

// stop the server
await serverState.close();
```

